Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Pat @chicken legs{16%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; rub with
@vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place
skin sides up on one side of a #baking sheet{}. Bake on top rack for
~{15%minutes} (we'll add more to the sheet then).

> TIP: Line your baking sheet with foil first for easy clean up.

While chicken bakes, wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate
@garlic{2%cloves}.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces, if necessary.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

Quarter @lime{1}.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{}. Add garlic and scallion
whites; cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big
pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to
serve.

Once chicken has baked 15 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Toss broccoli
on empty side of same sheet with @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.
(For 4 servings, leave chicken roasting; toss broccoli on a second baking
sheet and roast on middle rack.) Return to oven until broccoli is tender and
chicken is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes} more. Remove broccoli from sheet;
tent with foil to keep warm.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @hoisin sauce{4%tablespoon}, ginger, and
lime juice to taste. Once chicken is cooked through, remove from oven and brush
with half the glaze (save the rest for serving). Bake until glaze is tacky and
has dried out a bit, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).
Divide rice, chicken, and broccoli between plates. Sprinkle chicken and broccoli
with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.

> You may have some sesame seeds left over.

Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with remaining glaze and remaining lime
wedges on the side.